<section class="hero" id="top">
  <div class="hero-meta">
    <div class="hero-meta-item">
      <span class="hero-meta-label">Currently</span>
      <span class="hero-meta-value">Tony Blair Institute<br />for Global Change<br />Freetown, Sierra Leone</span>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta-item">
      <span class="hero-meta-label">Writing</span>
      <span class="hero-meta-value">Negotiating Intelligence<br />working paper, 2026</span>
    </div>
    <div class="hero-meta-item">
      <span class="hero-meta-label">Based</span>
      <span class="hero-meta-value">Freetown &amp; Accra</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="hero-main" id="main-content">
    <h1>
      I work on the<br />
      <span class="it">gap</span> between what<br />
      African states declare<br />
      about AI and what<br />
      they can <span class="it">actually do.</span>
    </h1>
    <p class="hero-sub">Digital policy advisor and governance researcher. Ten years inside West and East African ministries, development agencies, and implementation teams. Currently building the measurement instruments that the field of African AI governance does not yet have.</p>
